NNEWI – The leader of Anambra Vigilance Services in Onitsha North Local Government Area of Anambra State, Chief Chinedu Ihenko, has assured that Anambra State would not slide into a haven for criminals again. Ihenko made the assertion last Wednesday when he was bestowed with multiple awards by groups and organizations to honour him for his contributions to the security of life and property not only in Onitsha but the entire Anambra State. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He said that despite the challenges, they would continue to work to ensure in concert with other security operatives and stakeholders that criminals did not hijack Onitsha and its environs. Ihenko said, “Whatever you are doing, you are bound to face challenges. We have decided to do this job. It is a voluntary and humanitarian service to our people. “